        <abstract> 
            <p>Thanks JS for essays. CD read the French abstracts [of "Hemisepius", <hi rend="italic">K. Dan. Vidensk. Selsk. Skr. (Naturvidensk. Math. Afd.)</hi> 5th ser. 10 (1875): 463–82, and "Sepiadarium og Idiosepius", <hi rend="italic">K. Dan. Vidensk. Selsk. Skr. (Naturvidensk. Math. Afd.)</hi> 6th ser. 1 (1880–5): 211–42]. Hectocotylisation has always astonished him.</p> 
            <p>Wishes JS believed in evolution.</p>
        </abstract>
